RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 1 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 66. Maiden Special Weight Purse 12000. FOR MAIDENS, TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MOCOWBELL angled in entering the bend, closed the gap on the leader nearing the quarter pole, got through along the rail leaving the turn, moved clear inside the final furlong and held sway. TORTUGA ISLAND slow to get into racing stride, was climbing into the turn, settled into a better stride leaving the bend, angled out five wide upper stretch, made a strong move in the waning yards but came up short. CLOEY ATTACK pressed just outside JILL ATTTACK, took a slight lead upper stretch, did not relent when MOCOWBELL drew clear inside the last eighth but failed to have the needed late kick. MOONSHINE MOLLY forwardly placed, was three then four wide taking the bend, had an easy striking position with a furlong to go but also needed more deep stretch. JILL ATTACK displayed early speed from inside, floated out some leaving the turn, was overtaken from both sides, began to yield upper stretch and drifted out gradually the last seventy yards.

ENTRY.NAME: Jill Attack
ENTRY.COMMENT: inside speed, 2-path into stretch, flattened out last 1/8,drifted

ENTRY.NAME: Cloey Attack
ENTRY.COMMENT: 2-3 path, weakened late

ENTRY.NAME: Mocowbell
ENTRY.COMMENT: angled in turn, got thru inside leaving turn, clear 1/16, held

ENTRY.NAME: Moonshine Molly
ENTRY.COMMENT: 3-4 wide turn, evenly late

ENTRY.NAME: Tortuga Island
ENTRY.OWNER: Ritter Charles W and Becker Scott
ENTRY.COMMENT: slow into stride and climbing, angled 5 wide stretch, surged late

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 2 6F Dirt CR: 57. Maiden Special Weight Purse 12000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CARICIA hesitated then made a slight lunge from the gate, was rated in the early going, let out after two furlongs, progressed four wide, took the advantage when put to urging upper stretch, soon moved clear, lugged in some inside the final eighth, held a straight path the final sixteenth and maintained control under a mild drive. FERGIE ATTACK shared the early lead outside MO WANNA GO, moved ahead after a quarter mile, came two wide into the lane and could not hold back CARICIA the last furlong. HIGHTAILING IT moved outside FERGIE ATTACK early on, came into the stretch three wide and slowly yielded the final eighth. MO WANNA GO displayed early speed from inside, did not stay with FERGIE ATTACK after two furlongs and steadily faded through the lane.

ENTRY.NAME: Hightailing It
ENTRY.COMMENT: pressed outside, 3 wide turn, weakened late

ENTRY.NAME: Mo Wanna Go
ENTRY.COMMENT: inside speed, gave way last 1/4

ENTRY.NAME: Fergie Attack
ENTRY.COMMENT: vied between, 2 wide turn, not enough left

ENTRY.NAME: Caricia
ENTRY.OWNER: Ritter Charles W and Becker Scott
ENTRY.COMMENT: hesitated start, 4 wide turn, clear inside 1/8, mild drive

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 3 6F Dirt CR: 58. Claiming Purse 10000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since May 19 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $4,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: WINDIGO SPIRIT rated just off the inside, moved clear when allowed on the bend, came into the lane still just off the inside, drew away under urging and was kept to task until the final sixteenth. MY KINDA TETON prominent from outside from the beginning, lost ground five wide taking the turn, moved clear for second upper stretch then could only lengthen his hold on the place in the waning yards. MARY'S BOY void of speed, though urged early, was soon taken outside, lost ground four to six wide through the bend, altered out further for a clear path upper stretch, was no match for the top pair but got up for third in the late going. SAFE was an contender between horses on the backstretch, did not keep up three wide on the turn, was caught in traffic as he tried to advance in the lane, steadied behind BLUE TEARDROPS near the sixteenth marker, altered in some then outfinished the latter for fourth at the wire. BLUE TEARDROPS well placed from inside, began to flatten out for the drive and started drifting out deep stretch. THACKER FROMM failed to menace in a ground-saving trip. TOWN CRIER raced in contention between rivals for a half mile then began to fade. LORD SHAFTESBURY displayed early speed outside WINDIGO SPIRIT, did not stay with that one on the bend and gave way for the drive. HE'S A FINE MAN was prominent toward the outside on the backstretch, lost ground four to six wide taking the turn then quickly yielded.

ENTRY.NAME: Thacker Fromm
ENTRY.COMMENT: saved ground, no factor

ENTRY.NAME: Mary's Boy
ENTRY.COMMENT: lost ground, mild bid 7 wide

ENTRY.NAME: Blue Teardrops
ENTRY.COMMENT: well placed inside, flattened out stretch, drifted out late

ENTRY.NAME: Town Crier
ENTRY.COMMENT: 2-3 wide turn, gave way stretch

ENTRY.NAME: Windigo Spirit
ENTRY.COMMENT: rated between, inside turn, drew off under urging stretch

ENTRY.NAME: Lord Shaftesbury
ENTRY.COMMENT: vied between, 3-4 wide turn, gave way stretch

ENTRY.NAME: Safe
ENTRY.COMMENT: 3 wide turn, in traffic stretch, steadied 1/16

ENTRY.NAME: He's a Fine Man
ENTRY.COMMENT: 4-6 wide turn, gave way last 1/4

ENTRY.NAME: My Kinda Teton
ENTRY.COMMENT: advanced outside, 5 wide turn, 2nd best

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 4 6F Dirt CR: 69. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 23500. FOR (REGISTERED BRED AND/OR FOALED IN ILLINOIS) THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OR OPTIONAL CLAIMING 10,000 FOR HORSES THAT HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since May 19 A llowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000 (Claiming Races For $7,500 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DANZA TAXI a step slow at the break, was a bit rank leaving the chute, corrected, sent to gain the lead after the first eighth, widened command on the bend, put to urging upper stretch and kept ST. LOUIE LOUIE at bay. ST. LOUIE LOUIE prominent from outside, stayed in path three on the turn, was all out the final furlong, drifted out under left handed urging nearing the sixteenth marker then lugged in when switched to right handed pressure in the waning yards, was too late but clearly second best. TRUIST raced in contention from inside from the early going, angled out two wide with a furlong left, lacked the needed late kick but was easily best of the others. FAST CROSS TRAFFIC raced in the second flight between rivals then gave way for the drive. SENOR MIKE was a factor between horses for a quarter mile then began to fade. SKIP AWAY CARTER was a contender just off the rail for two furlongs, moved toward the outside after that for a clear path but had little to offer.

ENTRY.NAME: Danza Taxi
ENTRY.OWNER: Ritter Charles W and Becker Scott
ENTRY.COMMENT: sent to lead, inside, held on

ENTRY.NAME: Skip Away Carter
ENTRY.COMMENT: faded outside early

ENTRY.NAME: Truist
ENTRY.COMMENT: saved ground, angled 2 wide 1/8, evenly last 1/8

ENTRY.NAME: Senor Mike
ENTRY.COMMENT: between, thru early

ENTRY.NAME: Fast Cross Traffic
ENTRY.OWNER: The Estate of Kenneth H Hutchens
ENTRY.COMMENT: 2nd flight between, 2 wide turn, gave way stretch

ENTRY.NAME: St. Louie Louie
ENTRY.OWNER: Ritter Charles W and Becker Scott
ENTRY.COMMENT: 3 wide turn, weaved last 1/16

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 5 6F Dirt CR: 62. Claiming Purse 7500. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE IN 2023 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $3,200.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TEMPLUNA rated from inside, progressed along the rail on the bend, continued her bid just off the inside in the lane, took the advantage nearing the sixteenth marker and gradually edged ahead. COOKIN ROSES was reluctant to load, broke on top once the race began, showed the way just off the inside, floated out some entering the stretch and slowly wore down the final furlong. G CITY WARRIOR urged along early between rivals, did not keep up along the rail on the bend, regained a striking position upper stretch but found best stride too late inside the last eighth. SUPERTRIX was steadied back from crowding leaving the chute, taken to the outside, settled well back, was three wide on the turn, lost further ground fanning widest for the stretch run and gradually lugged in as she advanced the final furlong. LOUIE P chased while toward the outside, was three wide on the bend, swung outside BOBBIE TOO TOO entering the lane, was checked when caught in tight quarters between the latter and SUPERTRIX midstretch and had no late bid. BOBBIE TOO TOO hesitated at the break, moved up quickly to press the early leader from outside for a half mile then gave way. SWEET JUSTICE charged the gate just as it was about to open, then reared up and flipped over, losing her rider. There was a stewards' inquiry into SWEET JUSTICE'S start but after their review, no action was taken.

ENTRY.NAME: Supertrix
ENTRY.COMMENT: steadied early, lost ground, lugged in last 1/8

ENTRY.NAME: Templuna
ENTRY.COMMENT: rated inside, let out turn, edged ahead last 1/16

ENTRY.NAME: Cookin Roses
ENTRY.COMMENT: reluctant to load, 2-3 path speed, weakened late

ENTRY.NAME: G City Warrior
ENTRY.COMMENT: forwardly between, saved ground turn, gaining

ENTRY.NAME: Louie P
ENTRY.COMMENT: 3 wide 1/4, 5 wide into stretch, in tight 1/8, checked

ENTRY.NAME: Sweet Justice
ENTRY.COMMENT: reared in gate, flipped, lost rider

ENTRY.NAME: Bobbie too Too
ENTRY.COMMENT: hesitated start, 3-4 path turn, gave way stretch

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 6 6F Dirt CR: 78. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 14000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD NON-WINNERS OF A RACE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, WAIVER CLAIMING, STARTER OR IBF OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES OR OPTIONAL CLAIMING PRICE OF $5,000. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-w inners Of A Race Since May 19 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000 (Claiming Races For $4,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SHEZ STUCK UP pressed the pace from between horses, dropped back from close quarters after two furlongs, was just off the rail on the bend, began to fanned out nearing the end of a half mile, surged the final eighth and swept past FOGGY KITTEN with twenty yards to go. FOGGY KITTEN broke in stride, showed the way in hand from just off the inside, responded to encouragement upper stretch to lengthen command, was all out the last furlong but did not have enough left in the waning yards. LIL BIT TIPSEY pressed the early speed from outside on the back, took over second three wide on the bend, angled in some entering the lane and leveled off the last eighth. ENGLISH prominent from inside from the beginning, lacked a stretch rally. TROUBLE FINDS ME unruly in the gate, helped prompt the pace from between rivals on the backstretch, began to retreat two wide on the turn, floated out to path four into the lane and quickly gave way.

ENTRY.NAME: English
ENTRY.COMMENT: saved ground, no rally

ENTRY.NAME: Shez Stuck Up
ENTRY.OWNER: McDonnell Bernard P and McDonnell Myles D
ENTRY.COMMENT: retreated 2-path turn, surged 5-path last 1/8, got up in time

ENTRY.NAME: Foggy Kitten
ENTRY.COMMENT: broke in stride, saved ground, weakened late

ENTRY.NAME: Trouble Finds Me
ENTRY.COMMENT: unruly in gate, 2-4 path, gave way last 1/4

ENTRY.NAME: Lil Bit Tipsey
ENTRY.COMMENT: 3 wide 1/4, 2 wide into stretch, evenly last 1/8

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 7 6F Dirt CR: 86. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 14000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD NON-WINNERS OF A RACE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, WAIVER CLAIMING, STARTER OR IBF OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES OR OPTIONAL CLAIMING PRICE OF $5,000. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Si nce May 19 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000 (Claiming Races For $4,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BOOTDADDY JUSTICE was rated off the early speed from outside, commenced his bid four wide on the bend, was carried out further by TIZ APPROVED entering the lane, brushed by the latter midstretch but drew away under mild urging approaching the final sixteenth. BUREAU settled well off the pace on the backstretch, picked up his pace just off the rail on the turn, angled outside NOT AGAIN JACKIE midstretch and split rivals nearing the wire to get up for the place. NOT AGAIN JACKIE chased from inside, reached contention on the bend, floated out some into the lane, threatened with a furlong to go, battled for second in the late going but leveled off in the waning yards. TIZ APPROVED broke inward, was straightened and moved up quickly off the rail but inside rivals to vie for the lead, stayed just off the rail taking the turn, drifted out to path four entering the lane, drifted out some under left-handed pressure to brush with BOOTDADDY JUSTICE with a furlong to go, was corrected, fought to hold second nearing the last sixteenth but did not have enough left. TALIS PARK GRAD hesitated slightly and came out of the gate throwing his head, progressed from outside to gain a striking position four wide on the turn, was forced to lose further ground into the stretch and was closing in on the second flight inside the final furlong. MAC PANDOWDY soon trailed and failed to menace in a wide trip. MY LITTLE TIPSY displayed early speed outside TIZ APPROVED, was caught in tight quarters between the latter and BOOTDADDY JUSTICE near the quarter pole and gave way through the stretch.

ENTRY.NAME: Tiz Approved
ENTRY.COMMENT: speed off rail, 2-4 path turn, drifted 1/8, brushed, weakened

ENTRY.NAME: Not Again Jackie
ENTRY.COMMENT: advanced inside, 2-path into stretch, loomed 1/8, hung

ENTRY.NAME: Bureau
ENTRY.OWNER: Pohl Dennis and Gavilsky II Lawrence J
ENTRY.COMMENT: chased just off rail, angled out midstretch, split rivals late

ENTRY.NAME: Mac Pandowdy
ENTRY.COMMENT: wide trip, no factor

ENTRY.NAME: My Little Tipsy
ENTRY.COMMENT: vied outside, 3 wide turn, in tight 1/4, gave way

ENTRY.NAME: Bootdaddy Justice
ENTRY.COMMENT: rated outside, 4-5 path turn, brushed 1/8, drew off, mild drive

ENTRY.NAME: Talis Park Grad
ENTRY.COMMENT: threw head start, lost ground, best of rest
